title.narrative: DRRR/ EMERGENCY RESPONSE

description.narrative: Emergency Programme Implementation, which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Operations Support To Programme Delivery (Covid), Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid), Supply And Logistics, Supply And Logistics (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Communities, parents, caregivers and children have increased awareness of the consequences of violence and have the skills to protect children and women.

title.narrative: Emergency Programme Implementation

description.narrative: COVID-19 Pandemic continued to affect the entire population with >34,000 confirmed cases and 484 deaths. The RCCE campaign reached to 5 million population for awareness building and COVID vaccine demand generation. 1,294 Health workers were trained on RCCE, 10,642 community leaders received orientation and IEC materials for community awareness building on COVID-19, 823 health facilities received 1.5 million printed IEC materials for COVID-19 vaccination, and 800 front liners were engaged through UNICEF’s advocacy effort. Also, 356,000 people above 18 years of age were administered with COVID-19 vaccines. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/12/2021
